  Releasing a long-held breath, Mona as well as everyone else silently watched
  as the old teacher stormed out of the classroom, still muttering something to
  himself.

  Compared to the two girls forced to stand, Mona was definitely paying a lot
  more attention to the lesson. However, even she could not give a definite
  answer to the question from earlier, so the past 15 minutes had been quite
  hellish for her.

  "How unfortunate, right, Uta-chan?"

  The name of her friend echoing in the classroom immediately caught her
  attention.

  Mona turned around to see her friend, Kazugai Uta, still standing. Back when
  she was called, she had a troubled and worried expression, but it seemed all
  of those emotions were now replaced with nothing but tiredness.

  Standing near her was the same girl Uta seemed to talk with a lot. _"If I'm
  not mistaken, then her name is Rika... or something"_. The girl gave a wry
  smile to her friend, as if consoling Uta.

  "Well, it's always like this, I'm used to it now..."

  Uta sat down just like a robot shutting off. Thump. She briefly looked at her
  cell phone before seemingly being reminded of something. The sudden change on
  Uta's facial expression also made Mona recall something, too.

  _"My heart was filled with determination. Yes, I will draw the sword to kill
  this timid past self of mine, becoming someone that not only Uta and Mikoto,
  but I could even be proud of!"_

  She immediately turned around out of cringe. Even though those words from last
  night only echoed in her head, she felt as they were broadcasted over the
  school radio to everyone.

  Mona recalled more of the corny lines of hers while she was talking to herself
  the last night. The worrying thing was, since then, she had done absolutely
  nothing to reduce the distance between her and her new two friends.

  She thought of initiating the conversation in the morning, but ended up
  arriving at school barely on time.

  She intended to message something to either Uta or Mikoto, but her phone ended
  up running out of battery due to her forgetting to charge it the day before.

  And now, she was planning to go to the cafeteria with the two, but the biology
  teacher extending his period had almost erased the thought from her mind
  entirely. Not to mention that Mikoto seemed to have wandered elsewhere, so a
  three-person gathering at this point was clearly improbable.

  Just when Mona had decided to change herself, it seemed that everything was
  trying to steer her away from the path she envisioned.

  _"Yet, giving up here would be pathetic, right?"_

  As long as she could stay determined, chances were destined to pop up, no
  matter what.

  _"Right? It's not like this is the last time I'm gonna be with Uta and Mikoto
  or anything."_

  Moreover, it was only Mikoto who wandered elsewhere, as Uta seemed to have
  nothing coming up at all. A two-person lunch would still be a valuable chance
  to get close to Uta, too.

  Mona regained her confidence and brushed aside the unnecessary thoughts on her
  mind, before turning around for the second time.

  However, her friend was no longer within sight.

  Mona sighed. It seemed that God was messing with her yet again.

