  When Uta recalled the important task she planned for this lunch break, she
  immediately stood up from her seat.

  Yesterday, she could not sleep very well. The traumatic experience at the
  karaoke shop, well, "traumatic" seemed to be quite a strong word, but it was
  really like that for Uta, still haunted her until this very moment.

  It was exactly why she barely had any energy to focus on today's lessons,
  which coincidentally made her the prime target for that raging old man.

  However, everything would be resolved today.

  While deeply overthinking about a random interaction with a boy her class, Uta
  had unconsciously outlined a detailed plan on how to approach him. As she
  could not fall asleep, Uta decided to be a morning person for once and arrive
  school at seven, breaking her own personal record.

  Since there was no one awake at that time, and the few early birds she knew
  actually woke up early for a reason other than to message their friends, Uta
  found herself in a surreal peace.

  While she was on the hallway walking to class, she felt as if she was in a
  parallel world, in which no humans existed. The occasional noises from the
  nearby baseball stadium snapped her out of such thoughts, but the silence
  followed quickly reminded her of how lonely she was on this day.

  Unsurprisingly, she was the first to enter the classroom. While Mikoto
  had probably arrived school about 30 minutes sooner than her, it did not
  matter as Mikoto was heading directly to the running tracks.

  Uta went to sit at her place. Normally, she could use her classmate neighbors
  as anchors to instantly find her seat in class, but in this empty classroom,
  it did take her a little while to find her personal oasis.

  Even though she spent the whole night sleepless, her eyes remained wide open
  under the gentle sunlight coming from the window. Not even an ounce of
  sleepiness was she feeling, and she was slightly surprised.

  _"Maybe my eyes were able to rest even when I was not sleeping, I think?
  Anyway, it's good that I'm able to stay sharp for now."_

  Forgot to mention, but Uta headed to school early was not a decision she made
  just because she could not sleep. It was rather the first step of her grand
  plan for today.

  _"Now, I'll have to pay a little bit of attention to whoever comes to class
  next..."_

  She was waiting for someone. Otherwise, she would walk around the school while
  looking at random strands of the campus tapestry, while bringing along some
  random snacks to pass the time. Moreover, that someone was not a person of her
  gender, something that was rare to a socialable girl like Kazugai Uta.

  Yesterday, she had thought of contacting that _someone_, yet she could not
  find his name in the temporary class group chat. It was temporary because,
  well, that was a group that the most popular boys and girls her class
  originally made to chat together, but ended up getting quite a lot of members
  in the first few days when friendships formed.

  Currently, the group had 30 members out of the 40 students in class 1-E. It
  probably would take just another day or two until this became a proper MINE
  group for the whole class, with the most socially-awkward ones included just
  for the sake of completeness.

  The night before, she intended to settle everything via MINE, but she could
  not find his name in the member list. She double-checked, triple-checked, yet
  could not find anything. She almost resorted to messaging Nagi Tadano, the
  only one who seemed to be close with _that person_ in class, before deciding
  that it would be smarter to settle things privately.

  That was the exact reason why Uta's eyes were dashing back and forth between
  her smartphone screen and the classroom door every one or two minutes. Even
  though she did not think that anyone would arrive in the next fifteen minutes,
  a little safe would not do any harm.

